external_knowledge:
Cumulative sales refer to the total sales over a specified period; 
Available stock refers to the current quantity of products in the inventory; 
Top cumulative sales means the highest total sales; 
Product offer price is the current price at which the product is being offered; 
Restock date is the date when the product was last restocked.

sql:
SELECT product_name, product_offer_price, product_strike_price, is_active, AVG(product_offer_price) OVER () AS average_offer_price
FROM products
WHERE is_active = 1;
